logical /ˈlɒdʒɪkəl/

1. ADJ In a logical argument or method of reasoning, each step must be true if the step before it is true. 逻辑的 (观点或推理方式) 

例： Only when each logical step has been checked by other mathematicians will the proof be accepted. 只有在每个逻辑步骤都由其他数学家验证之后，该证明才会被接受。 

2. logically ADV 逻辑地 

例： My professional training has taught me to look at things logically. 我的专业训练教会了我逻辑地看待事物。 

3. ADJ The logical conclusion or result of a series of facts or events is the only one which can come from it, according to the rules of logic. 合乎逻辑的 (结论或结果等) 

例： If the climate gets drier, then the logical conclusion is that even more drought will occur. 如果气候变得更干燥，那么符合逻辑的结论就是甚至更多的旱灾将会发生。 

4. logically ADV 合乎逻辑地 [ADV with v] 

例： From that it followed logically that he would not be meeting Hildegarde. 从那一点看来，他不会见希尔德加德是合乎逻辑的。 

5. ADJ Something that is logical seems reasonable or sensible in the circumstances. 合理的; 明智的 

例： Connie suddenly struck her as a logical candidate. 她突然想到康尼是个合适的人选。 

例： There was a logical explanation. 存在一个合理的解释。 

6. logically ADV 合理地; 明智地 

例： This was the one possibility I hadn't taken into consideration, though logically I should have. 这是一种我没有考虑到的可能性，尽管按道理我本该考虑到的。

